            Geographical Constituencies (Legislative Council) Order
            1999</docTitle><enactingFormula role="empoweringSection">(<ref href="/hk/cap542/s18">Cap. 542, sections 18</ref> and <ref href="/hk/cap542/s19">19</ref>)</enactingFormula><sourceNote>(Enacting provision omitted—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><commencementNote>[1 January 2000]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403411496_002" name="s1" reason="omittedAsSpent" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="omitted" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><sourceNote>(Omitted as spent—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438403411496_004" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Interpretation</heading><leadIn>In this Order—</leadIn><def name="ApprovedMap"><leadIn><term>approved
                    map</term>
                    (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">獲批准地圖</term>) means the map or maps—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438413203161_019" name="a" temporalId="s2_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>submitted together with the report referred to in <ref>section 18(1)(a)</ref> of the Electoral Affairs Commission Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap541">Cap. 541</ref>) by the Electoral Affairs Commission to the Chief Executive on 30 October 1999;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413203161_027" name="b" temporalId="s2_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>specified in column 4 of the <ref>Schedule</ref>;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413203161_035" name="c" temporalId="s2_c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content>identified by reference to a plan number (Plan No.) prefixed “LCCA”;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413203176_005" name="d" temporalId="s2_d"><num value="d">(d)</num><content>approved by the Chief Executive in Council on 16 November 1999; and</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413203176_013" name="e" temporalId="s2_e"><num value="e">(e)</num><content>deposited in the office of the Electoral Registration Officer;</content></paragraph></def><def name="AreaCode"><leadIn><term>area
                    code</term>
                    (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">地區代號</term>), in relation to an area declared to be
                a geographical constituency in this Order, means the code—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438413203176_027" name="a" temporalId="s2_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>prefixed “LC” and followed by a number;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413203176_035" name="b" temporalId="s2_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>mentioned opposite that area in column 3 of the <ref>Schedule</ref>; and</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413203176_043" name="c" temporalId="s2_c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content>coloured red and described as “Recommended 2000 Legislative Council Constituency Area Code” in the legend of the relevant approved map;</content></paragraph></def><def name="ConstituencyBoundary">
            <leadIn><term>constituency
                    boundary</term>
                    (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">選區分界</term>), in relation to an area declared to be
                a geographical constituency in this Order, means—</leadIn>
            <paragraph id="ID_1438413203176_057" name="a" temporalId="s2_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>the boundary represented by the unbroken edging coloured red delineating,
                    or partially delineating, that area and described as “Recommended 2000
                    Legislative Council Constituency Area Boundary (coincides with District
                    Boundary)” in the legend of the relevant approved map; or</content></paragraph>
            <paragraph id="ID_1438413203192_006" name="b" temporalId="s2_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><leadIn>where any part of a district boundary—</leadIn><subparagraph id="ID_1438413203192_014" name="i" temporalId="s2_b_i"><num value="i">(i)</num><content>coincides with the HKSAR boundary; and</content></subparagraph><subparagraph id="ID_1438413203192_022" name="ii" temporalId="s2_b_ii"><num value="ii">(ii)</num><subparagraph id="ID_1438413203192_024" name="A" role="subSubParagraph" temporalId="s2_b_ii_A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content>joins or abuts any boundary, mentioned in paragraph (a), partially
                            delineating that area; or</content></subparagraph><subparagraph id="ID_1438413203192_031" name="B" role="subSubParagraph" temporalId="s2_b_ii_B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content>circumscribes or otherwise partially delineates that
                            area,</content></subparagraph></subparagraph><continued>that part of the district boundary, and that boundary, mentioned in
                    paragraph (a), partially delineating that area;</continued></paragraph>
            
        </def><def name="DistrictBoundary"><term>district
                boundary</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">地方行政區分界</term>) means the boundary represented by the
            unbroken edging coloured green and described as “District Boundary” in the legend of the
            relevant approved map;</def><def name="HKSARBoundary"><term>HKSAR
                boundary</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">特區界線</term>) means the boundary of the administrative
            division of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region promulgated by the Order of the
            State Council of the People’s Republic of China No. 221 dated 1 July 1997 and published
            as S.S. No. 5 to
            Gazette No.
            6/1997
            of the Gazette.</def></section><section id="ID_1438403411512_002" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Declaration of Legislative Council geographical constituencies</heading><content>Each area named in column 2 of the <ref>Schedule</ref> and delineated on the approved map mentioned opposite that area in column 4 of the <ref>Schedule</ref> is declared to be a geographical constituency for the purpose of an election to elect the Members for the second term of office of the Legislative Council, and the name of the geographical constituency is specified opposite that area in column 5 of the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403411527_002" name="s4" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>Number of Members to be returned for each geographical constituency</heading><content>For each area declared to be a geographical constituency in this Order, the number of Members to be returned at the general election for the second term of office of the Legislative Council is specified opposite the name of the geographical constituency in column 6 of the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></section><schedule id="ID_1438403411543_001" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note class="align_right" role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap542G/s2">ss. 2</ref>, <ref href="/hk/cap542G/s3">3</ref> &amp; <ref href="/hk/cap542G/s4">4</ref>]<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></note><content>
            
